    "content": "🔧 Tool: Task\nInput: {\n  \"description\": \"Explore agent session and thinking indicator\",\n  \"subagent_type\": \"Explore\",\n  \"prompt\": \"I need to understand how the agent chat view handles session switching, thinking indicators, and streaming state. Specifically:\\n\\n1. How does the agent view handle switching between chat sessions (going to \\\"new chat\\\" and back to an existing chat)?\\n2. How is the \\\"thinking indicator\\\" (blue dot) implemented and when is it shown/hidden?\\n3. How is the streaming/loading state managed when switching sessions?\\n4. What happens to the WebSocket event listeners when switching sessions?\\n\\nPlease thoroughly explore these files and their relationships:\\n- apps/ui/src/components/views/agent-view/ (all files)\\n- apps/ui/src/components/views/agent-view/hooks/use-agent-session.ts\\n- apps/ui/src/components/views/agent-view/components/thinking-indicator.tsx\\n- apps/ui/src/components/views/agent-view/components/message-list.tsx\\n- apps/ui/src/components/views/agent-view/components/session-selector.tsx\\n- apps/ui/src/store/app-store.ts (look for agent/session related state)\\n- apps/ui/src/hooks/ (any hooks related to agent sessions)\\n\\nFor each file, I need to understand:\\n- The key state variables and how they change\\n- How session switching works\\n- How the thinking/streaming indicator state is managed\\n- Any race conditions or state reset issues when switching sessions\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Bash\nInput: {\n  \"command\": \"find \\\"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\\\" -type f -name \\\"*.tsx\\\" -o -name \\\"*.ts\\\" | head -20\",\n  \"description\": \"List all files in agent-view directory\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\\\\hooks\\\\use-agent-session.ts\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\\\\components\\\\thinking-indicator.tsx\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\\\\components\\\\message-list.tsx\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\\\\components\\\\session-selector.tsx\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\\\\components\\\\chat-area.tsx\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\\\\components\\\\agent-header.tsx\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Bash\nInput: {\n  \"command\": \"find \\\"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\\\" -name \\\"agent-view.tsx\\\" -o -name \\\"index.tsx\\\" | grep -E \\\"(index|agent-view)\\\"\",\n  \"description\": \"Find main agent view component file\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Glob\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"**/agent-view/agent-view.tsx\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Bash\nInput: {\n  \"command\": \"ls -la \\\"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\\\\*.tsx\\\" 2>/dev/null | head -20\",\n  \"description\": \"List tsx files in agent-view root\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Glob\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"**/agent-view/*.tsx\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Glob\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"agent-view.tsx\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view.tsx\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\store\\\\app-store.ts\",\n  \"limit\": 200\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"lastSelectedSession|setLastSelectedSession|getLastSelectedSession\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\store\\\\app-store.ts\",\n  \"output_mode\": \"content\",\n  \"head_limit\": 50\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Glob\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"**/use-electron-agent.ts\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\hooks\\\\use-electron-agent.ts\",\n  \"limit\": 300\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\hooks\\\\use-electron-agent.ts\",\n  \"offset\": 300,\n  \"limit\": 200\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\\\\hooks\\\\use-agent-scroll.ts\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\\\\hooks\\\\use-file-attachments.ts\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\\\\input-area\\\\agent-input-area.tsx\",\n  \"limit\": 100\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"unsubscribeRef|onStream|sessionId !== sessionId\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\hooks\\\\use-electron-agent.ts\",\n  \"output_mode\": \"content\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\hooks\\\\use-electron-agent.ts\",\n  \"offset\": 499,\n  \"limit\": 150\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Bash\nInput: {\n  \"command\": \"cd \\\"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\" && git log --oneline --all -20\",\n  \"description\": \"Show recent commits to understand context\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\\\\components\\\\message-bubble.tsx\",\n  \"limit\": 150\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\\\\components\\\\empty-states.tsx\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Bash\nInput: {\n  \"command\": \"cd \\\"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\" && git diff HEAD -- apps/ui/src/components/views/agent-view/ 2>/dev/null | head -200\",\n  \"description\": \"Show recent changes to agent-view files\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Bash\nInput: {\n  \"command\": \"cd \\\"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\" && find . -name \\\"*.test.ts\\\" -path \\\"*/agent*\\\" 2>/dev/null | head -5\",\n  \"description\": \"Find test files for agent\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\\\\hooks\\\\use-agent-session.ts\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\\\\components\\\\message-list.tsx\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view\\\\components\\\\thinking-indicator.tsx\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\agent-view.tsx\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"isProcessing|setIsProcessing|isRunning\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\hooks\",\n  \"output_mode\": \"files_with_matches\"\n}\n\n🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\hooks\\\\use-electron-agent.ts\"\n}\nNow I have a thorough understanding of the bug. Let me generate the specification.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Problem Statement\n\nWhen using the Agent Runner chat, if a user sends a message (triggering an AI response), then navigates to a new chat session and back to the original session, the UI appears frozen with no visual indicator that the AI is still thinking. The `isProcessing` state is correctly restored via `getHistory()` (line 214 of `use-electron-agent.ts`), but there is a **race condition**: the `initialize()` function calls `api.agent.start()` first, then separately calls `api.agent.getHistory()` to check running state. During the gap between these two async calls, the `isProcessing` state remains `false` (its initial value), causing the ThinkingIndicator to not render, making the UI appear frozen until the agent eventually responds.\n\n## 2. User Story\n\nAs a **user of the Agent Runner**, I want **to see the \"Thinking...\" indicator (animated blue dots) when I switch back to a chat session where the AI is still processing**, so that **I know the AI is actively working and the UI hasn't frozen**.\n\n## 3. Acceptance Criteria\n\n- **Happy Path**: GIVEN the user has sent a message in Session A and the AI is processing, WHEN the user switches to a new session and then back to Session A, THEN the ThinkingIndicator (blue animated dots with \"Thinking...\" text) is displayed immediately upon returning to Session A.\n\n- **Happy Path - Completion**: GIVEN the user has returned to a session where the AI was processing, WHEN the AI completes its response, THEN the ThinkingIndicator disappears and the completed response is displayed normally.\n\n- **Edge Case - Already Completed**: GIVEN the user switched away from Session A and the AI finished responding while they were away, WHEN the user switches back to Session A, THEN the completed response is shown with no ThinkingIndicator.\n\n- **Edge Case - Rapid Switching**: GIVEN the user rapidly switches between multiple sessions, WHEN arriving at a session with active processing, THEN the ThinkingIndicator state is correct (no stale state from previous sessions).\n\n- **Error Handling**: GIVEN the `getHistory()` call fails, WHEN the user switches to a session, THEN the `isProcessing` falls back to `false` (existing behavior preserved).\n\n## 4. Technical Context\n\n| Aspect | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Affected Files | `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-electron-agent.ts` |\n| Dependencies | None (existing APIs only) |\n| Constraints | Must not break existing stream event handling or queue processing |\n| Patterns to Follow | Existing `useState`/`useEffect` patterns in `use-electron-agent.ts` |\n\n## 5. Non-Goals\n\n- Changing how session switching or persistence works\n- Modifying the ThinkingIndicator component itself\n- Adding new API endpoints\n- Changing the stream event subscription model\n\n## 6. Implementation Tasks\n\n```tasks\n## Phase 1: Core Fix\n\n- [ ] T001: Eliminate race condition by resetting isProcessing to false at start of session switch AND immediately setting it based on getHistory result before any re-render gap | File: apps/ui/src/hooks/use-electron-agent.ts\n```\n\n## 7. Success Metrics\n\n- When switching back to a session where the AI is still processing, the ThinkingIndicator (blue dots + \"Thinking...\") renders immediately\n- When switching to a session where the AI has finished, no ThinkingIndicator is shown\n- No regressions in normal message sending, streaming, or session switching behavior\n\n## 8. Risks & Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| getHistory call could be slow, causing delayed indicator | The indicator should show based on the result — the key fix is ensuring no gap where isProcessing is incorrectly false |\n| Stream events arriving before getHistory completes | The stream event handler already sets isProcessing=true on 'started' event, and session filtering ensures correctness |",
